title: Why people need poetry

aws-transcripts.transcript: I read poetry all the time and write about it frequently and take poems apart to see how they work. Because I'm a word person. I understand the world best, most fully inwards rather than, say, pictures or numbers. And when I have a new experience or a new feeling, I'm a little frustrated until I can try to put it into words. I think I've always been that way. I devoured science fiction as a child. I still do, and I thought poems by Andrew Marvell and Matthew Arnold and Emily Dickinson and William Butler Yates because they were quoted in science fiction and I love their sounds.
